Ethnographical Tunisian crochet, its essential elements, materials, techniques in Estonian examples.
NB! Foreign students are expected to:
*	Have good manual skills and previous basic experience in certain textile techniques;
*	Be prepared to purchase materials and a few tools.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Students will learn Estonian ethnographic techniques related to Tunisian crocheting.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon passing the subject, the student: - is knowledgeable about the spread of Tunisian crocheting in Estonian folk textile heritage at the turn of the 19th and 20th centuries. - has acquired the technique-based skills. - is able to prepare a methodological study material. - is able to combine the technique with different types of embroidery.
